### Prisma Schema Initialization (Prisma)

Source: https://github.com/prisma/prisma/blob/7.5.0/packages/migrate/src/__tests__/fixtures/old-migrate/migrations/20201019093934-init/README.md

This snippet defines the initial Prisma schema for the '20201019093934-init' migration. It configures a SQLite datasource and the Prisma Client JS generator, along with a 'Blogss' model.

```Prisma
datasource my_db {
  provider = "sqlite"
  url = "***"
}

generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client-js"
  output   = "@prisma/client"
}

model Blogss {
  id          Int @id
  viewCount20 Int
}
```

--------------------------------

### Prisma Schema Definition

Source: https://github.com/prisma/prisma/blob/7.5.0/README.md

Defines the data source, generator, and data models for a Prisma project. This schema configures the database connection and generates the Prisma Client, specifying the structure of your application's data models like 'Post' and 'User'.

```prisma
// Data source
datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
}

// Generator
generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client"
  output   = "../generated"
}

// Data model
model Post {
  id        Int     @id @default(autoincrement())
  title     String
  content   String?
  published Boolean @default(false)
  author    User?   @relation(fields:  [authorId], references: [id])
  authorId  Int?
}

model User {
  id    Int     @id @default(autoincrement())
  email String  @unique
  name  String?
  posts Post[]
}
```

--------------------------------

### Define Prisma Client Schema Template

Source: https://github.com/prisma/prisma/blob/7.5.0/GEMINI.md

Provides a schema template for functional tests, allowing dynamic schema generation based on the current provider in the test matrix.

```typescript
import { testMatrix } from '../_utils/testMatrix';

export default testMatrix.setupSchema(({ provider }) => `
  datasource db {
    provider = "${provider}"
    url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
  }

  model User {
    id Int @id @default(autoincrement())
  }
`);
```

--------------------------------

### Define Prisma Schema Template

Source: https://github.com/prisma/prisma/blob/7.5.0/AGENTS.md

Creates a dynamic schema template for functional tests based on the current provider in the matrix.

```prisma
testMatrix.setupSchema(({ provider }) => `
  datasource db {
    provider = "${provider}"
    url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
  }

  model User {
    id   Int    @id @default(autoincrement())
    name String
  }
`);
```

### Prisma 7 direction

Source: https://github.com/prisma/prisma/blob/7.5.0/CLAUDE.md

Prisma 7 introduces a significant architectural shift by moving away from 'schema.prisma' datasource URLs and 'env()' variables toward a centralized 'prisma.config.ts' file. This transition requires that commands, tests, and fixtures retrieve connection settings from 'PrismaConfigInternal.datasource' rather than relying on CLI flags or environment variables. Notably, SQLite datasource URLs now resolve relative to the configuration file rather than the schema file. As part of this evolution, automatic '.env' file loading is being removed, and CLI tools are being updated to prioritize config-based resolution over traditional '--schema' or '--url' flags.

